# AWS Setup Steps

1. Create VPC
2. Create Public and Private Subnets
3. Attach Internet Gateway to Public Subnet
4. Create NAT Gateway in Public Subnet
5. Configure Route Tables:
   - Public subnet → Internet Gateway
   - Private subnet → NAT Gateway
6. Launch EC2 in Private Subnet
7. Configure Security Groups:
   - Allow HTTP (80)
   - Allow SSH (22) if needed
8. Upload website files to EC2
9. Run server:
   python3 -m http.server 8000
10. Create Application Load Balancer
11. Configure Target Group (port 8000)
12. Attach EC2 instance
13. Access site via Load Balancer DNS
